üî• Perfect ‚Äî now we‚Äôre moving into dynamic inter-component data sharing and real-time updates, which is where Angular really shines.

We‚Äôll make your Travel Details and Approvals pages fully interactive and connected:

‚∏ª

üß≠ Final Goal

Page	What it does
Travel Details	Shows all submitted travels with a Status column (Approval Pending, Approved, or Rejected)
Approvals	Shows the same table + 2 buttons per row (Approve, Reject) that update the travel‚Äôs status dynamically everywhere

‚úÖ No backend yet ‚Äî everything stays synced through your shared TravelService.
‚úÖ Works instantly between both components.

‚∏ª

üü© STEP 1: Update your service ‚Äì travel.ts

Make your existing service stateful and reactive by using an RxJS BehaviorSubject, so updates reflect in both components automatically.

import { Injectable } from '@angular/core';
import { BehaviorSubject } from 'rxjs';

@Injectable({
  providedIn: 'root'
})
export class TravelService {
  private travelList: any[] = [];
  private travelSubject = new BehaviorSubject<any[]>(this.travelList);

  travel$ = this.travelSubject.asObservable();

  addTravel(detail: any) {
    detail.status = 'Approval Pending';
    this.travelList.push(detail);
    this.travelSubject.next(this.travelList);
  }

  getTravels() {
    return this.travelList;
  }

  updateStatus(uid: string, status: string) {
    const travel = this.travelList.find(t => t.uid === uid);
    if (travel) {
      travel.status = status;
      this.travelSubject.next(this.travelList);
    }
  }
}

‚úÖ This service now:
	‚Ä¢	Initializes an array of travels
	‚Ä¢	Emits updates using BehaviorSubject
	‚Ä¢	Lets you change travel status via updateStatus()

‚∏ª

üü© STEP 2: Update travel-details.ts

import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { TravelService } from '../services/travel';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-travel-details',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [CommonModule],
  templateUrl: './travel-details.html',
  styleUrls: ['./travel-details.css']
})
export class TravelDetailsComponent implements OnInit {
  travelList: any[] = [];

  constructor(private travelService: TravelService) {}

  ngOnInit() {
    this.travelService.travel$.subscribe(data => {
      this.travelList = data;
    });
  }
}


